---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../../../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
import FAQ from '../../../components/FAQ.astro';
import PickCard from '../../../components/PickCard.astro';
import { articleSchema, breadcrumbSchema, faqSchema, itemListSchema } from '../../../lib/schema';

const title = 'Worx Lawn Mowers UK - Cordless & Landroid Robot Reviewed';
const description = 'Independent reviews of Worx lawn mowers. PowerShare 20V/40V cordless platform and the Landroid Vision wire-free robot mower compared.';
const path = '/brands/worx/';
const datePublished = '2026-05-10';

const crumbs = [{ name: 'Home', url: '/' }, { name: 'Brands', url: '/brands/' }, { name: 'Worx', url: path }];

const picks = [
  { rank: 1, name: 'Worx Landroid Vision M800', brand: 'Worx', bestFor: 'budget wire-free robot mower', rating: 4.2, rrp: '£999', reviewUrl: '/reviews/worx-landroid-vision-m800/', pros: ['No perimeter wire - camera-led', 'Cheapest serious wire-free robot', 'Slots into Worx 20V battery ecosystem'], cons: ['Camera struggles in heavy tree shade', 'Needs two charges for 800 m²'], verdict: 'The most affordable way into wire-free robot mowing in 2026. Vision identifies grass vs flower bed via camera in real time - clever when it works. Best for regularly mown 400-600 m² lawns in good light.' },
  { rank: 2, name: 'Worx WG779E.2', brand: 'Worx', bestFor: 'twin-20V cordless on a budget', rating: 4.3, rrp: '£249', reviewUrl: '/brands/worx/', pros: ['Twin-20V (40V output) at this price', '34 cm deck', 'PowerShare batteries cross-compatible with 80+ Worx tools'], cons: ['Plastic deck flexes', 'Smaller cut than rivals at this price'], verdict: 'A cheap-and-cheerful cordless mower from the Worx PowerShare 20V platform - same batteries that run the Worx hedge trimmer, drill, and so on. Build is mid-tier; price is genuinely competitive.' },
];

const faqs = [
  { q: 'Are Worx lawn mowers any good?', a: 'For the price, yes - Worx sits between Ryobi and budget no-name brands. The build quality is mid-tier, the PowerShare battery ecosystem has 80+ tools (smaller than Ryobi but real), and the Landroid Vision is genuinely the best budget wire-free robot mower on the market in 2026.' },
  { q: 'What is the Worx PowerShare battery system?', a: 'PowerShare is Worx\'s shared 20V battery platform - drills, mowers, hedge trimmers, blowers, leaf vacuums, even a cordless pressure washer all use the same battery. Higher-output tools (mowers, brushcutters) take two batteries for 40V combined output. Smaller than Ryobi ONE+ or Bosch Power for All but covers most domestic gardening tools.' },
  { q: 'Worx Landroid Vision vs Husqvarna Automower - which is better?', a: 'Different jobs. The Landroid Vision is wire-free (no boundary cable) and £400-£800 cheaper. The Husqvarna Automower 305 needs boundary cable but the firmware is 11+ years more mature and the build is properly premium. Vision is the better choice if you hate the idea of cable laying or have an irregular garden; Automower is the safer choice if reliability over a decade matters more than installation effort.' },
  { q: 'Where are Worx tools made?', a: 'Worx is owned by Positec, a Chinese power-tool manufacturer that also makes Rockwell-branded tools. Design is Chinese; manufacturing is Chinese. Build quality is consistent across the range and noticeably better than no-name Amazon brands.' },
  { q: 'Can the Worx Landroid Vision really mow without a boundary wire?', a: 'Yes - it uses a front-facing camera plus on-board AI to identify grass vs flower beds vs gravel in real time. You set virtual boundaries in the app. It works well in good light on lawns with clear grass-to-non-grass transitions. It struggles in heavy shade, on lawns with very long grass that obscures the boundary, and right after heavy rain.' },
];

const schema = [
  breadcrumbSchema(crumbs),
  articleSchema({ headline: title, description, url: path, datePublished }),
  faqSchema(faqs),
  itemListSchema({ name: 'Best Worx lawn mowers 2026', url: path, items: picks.map((p, i) => ({ position: i+1, name: p.name, url: p.reviewUrl })) }),
];
---
<BaseLayout {title} {description} {schema}>
  <article class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-10">
    <Breadcrumbs items={crumbs} />
    <header class="mb-8">
      <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-grass-700 uppercase tracking-wide mb-2">Brand guide · Updated May 2026</p>
      <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-soil-900 leading-tight">Worx Lawn Mowers</h1>
      <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
        Worx is the brand that quietly punched above its weight in 2024 by launching the cheapest serious wire-free robot mower on the market - the Landroid Vision. They\'ve also been making solid mid-tier cordless mowers on the PowerShare 20V platform for years. Worx is what Ryobi was a decade ago: not the best on any single metric, but consistently the best price-to-quality ratio in its category.
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="prose-mowers">
      <h2 id="best">Best Worx lawn mowers</h2>
      <div class="space-y-6 mt-6">{picks.map((p) => <PickCard {...p} />)}</div>

      <h2 id="range">The Worx range explained</h2>
      <p>
        Worx has two product lines worth knowing. <strong>PowerShare</strong> - the 20V cordless platform with mowers, hedge trimmers, blowers and 80+ other garden and DIY tools all sharing batteries. <strong>Landroid</strong> - the robot mower range, including the boundary-cable Landroid M and L, and the wire-free Landroid Vision. Worx doesn\'t make corded electric, petrol, or hover mowers.
      </p>

      <h2 id="vs-rivals">Where Worx fits vs rivals</h2>
      <p>
        On cordless, <a href="/brands/ryobi/">Ryobi</a> is the obvious rival - bigger ecosystem (200+ tools to Worx\'s 80+), broadly similar price, similar build quality. On robots, <a href="/brands/husqvarna/">Husqvarna</a> Automower is the premium alternative; <strong>Mammotion Luba 2</strong> is the wire-free alternative at a higher price. The right buyer for Worx: someone who wants a wire-free robot under £1,000, or someone shopping price-first cordless without a strong existing battery loyalty.
      </p>

      <h2 id="related">Related guides</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="/robot-lawn-mowers/">Best robot lawn mowers</a></li>
        <li><a href="/robot-lawn-mowers/no-perimeter-wire/">Best wire-free robot lawn mowers</a></li>
        <li><a href="/cordless-lawn-mowers/">Best cordless lawn mowers</a></li>
        <li><a href="/brands/ryobi/">Ryobi lawn mowers</a></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <FAQ {faqs} />
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
